This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category since it deals with the problem of recommending blogs to users based on their interests. It also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as Factorization Machines (FM) to improve the recommendation quality. 

The paper may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category since it deals with the problem of recommending blogs to users in a social network platform like Tumblr. 

The Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is also likely since the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach to improve blog recommendation. 

The Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category is another possibility since the paper focuses on improving the user experience of mobile users in Tumblr by providing better blog recommendations. 

Finally, the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category may also be relevant since the paper may involve the analysis of textual data from blogs and app usage logs to extract user interests.
